message.entry: The "{0}" property must be a logical array.
The number of elements in the "x" input vector must match the number of Free elements in the parameter.
The number of elements in the "index" input vector must match the number of Free elements in the parameter.
The parameter object must be a scalar.
The "{0}" property must be a positive integer.
The "{0}" property must be a nonnegative real value.
The "{0}" property must be a character vector.
The "{0}" property must be a character vector or cell array of character vectors.
The "{0}" property must be a cell array of character vectors.
The "{0}" property dimensions must not change.
The ValueSet property must be a numeric, logical, or string vector.
The Value property must be an element from the ValueSet property.
The Type property must be one of '{''Input'', ''Output'', ''InOut'', ''OutIn'', ''None''}.
The "Info" property must be a struct array with the same dimension as the "Value" property. The struct array must have "Label" and "Unit" fields.
Setting the "{0}" property of the "{1}" class is not allowed.
Changing the parameter name replaces the private parameterID property with a new ID object and may cause unexpected results.
